folder: Greenpoint Avenue & Manhattan Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Greenpoint Ave., at the N.E. corner of Manhattan Ave., showing the building which housed the 7th Precinct Police Station in 1880; now (1929) it is occupied by the Board of Transportation operating the city's subway system.

September 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

folder: Manhattan Avenue & Greenpoint Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Manhattan Avenue, south from Greenpoint Avenue, showing at the S.E. corner the Corn Exchange Bank. On the same side of the street is seen the spire of St. Anthony's Roman Catholic Church.

P. L. Sperr

July 25, 1939

folder: Manhattan Avenue & Greenpoint Avenue, Queens, NY
text:
910 Manhattan Avenue, east side, north of Greenpoint Avenue, showing in the center of the view the American Theatre. The building partially seen at the right houses the Board of Transportation of the City Subway System.

July 25, 1939

P. L. Sperr
